Scotland’s independent schools maintain high standards of learning, and in 2018 they again received excellent exam results, which are complemented by individual and collective success in sports, art, music and other fields.
These schools, which have over 30,000 students across Scotland, are represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCSE). They aim to provide the best level of services to students and their parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare students for further and higher education, their chosen careers, and make them citizens of the world.
As an educational sector that can design and implement an individual school curriculum, we see that modern languages continue to be a popular and desirable subject to choose from in schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If you speak to a person in a language they understand, they perceive it with their mind.
If you talk to her in her native language, she takes it with her heart.”
This is a powerful reminder that we cannot use only English if we want to build relationships and trust with people from other countries.
From the latest exam results this year, we can see that independent language schools are leading in the rankings of subjects with the best grades.
In total, 68% of students who studied foreign languages received a higher score of A.
Data collected from 74 SRNS schools showed that 72% of students received a higher A score from Chinese, and a further 72% of those learning German, 69% of those learning French, and 63% of those learning Spanish also received an A.
