Later, he rushed to the firing line and with "desperate courage" led the line ahead, before this one broke through to the field gun and destroyed three guns of the enemy unit.
Lt. Col. Vann was shot dead by a German sniper on October 4, 1918, just over a month before the war ended.
Michael Vann, 72, said his grandfather had done something he himself would never have been able to repeat and deserved respect.
He and his brother Dr. James Vann laid a wreath after a parade led by the Brentwood Imperial Youth Band.
